<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-23"><hi rend="italic">May 23, 1896</hi></date>.
                                (Received June 5.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 522.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your telegram of the 18th instant.</p>
                        <p>Acting in accordance therewith, the case will not be submitted for
                            consideration to the Spanish Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>